9
00:01:29,125 --> 00:01:37,333
♪

10
00:01:37,416 --> 00:01:39,375
♪

11
00:01:41,791 --> 00:01:44,458
[moans]

12
00:01:44,541 --> 00:01:45,666
[sighs]

13
00:01:45,750 --> 00:01:46,791
Huh?

14
00:01:46,875 --> 00:01:48,583
[TERUHASHI]
What're you doing in here?

15
00:01:48,666 --> 00:01:50,166
Ciao, babe.

16
00:01:50,250 --> 00:01:52,291
[TERUHASHI] Don't "ciao, babe!"
What were you doing in my bed?

17
00:01:52,375 --> 00:01:54,125
Nothing, I swear.
I was just tired,

18
00:01:54,208 --> 00:01:55,375
so I laid down
for a minute.

19
00:01:55,458 --> 00:01:56,750
Why didn't you use
your bed?

20
00:01:56,833 --> 00:01:59,375
I'm your brother,
It's not a big deal.

21
00:01:59,458 --> 00:02:00,708
I need to talk to you.

22
00:02:00,791 --> 00:02:02,583
Fine, but step outside.
I gotta change.

23
00:02:02,666 --> 00:02:04,333
Oh, I see.
That's the problem.

24
00:02:04,416 --> 00:02:06,083
I don't want you
seeing me change.

25
00:02:06,166 --> 00:02:07,958
Sure, I'll put my hands
over my eyes.

26
00:02:08,041 --> 00:02:09,458
You're just opening
them wider!

27
00:02:09,541 --> 00:02:11,750
I've had enough of you!
Get out of my room!

28
00:02:11,833 --> 00:02:14,375
So that's what happened.
And Kokomi hasn't said

29
00:02:14,458 --> 00:02:15,833
a single word to me
since.

30
00:02:15,916 --> 00:02:17,041
[SAIKI]
Go home, perv!

31
00:02:17,125 --> 00:02:18,416
It's a
lovers' quarrel.

32
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:20,000
You know
what that is?

33
00:02:20,083 --> 00:02:21,541
It's a minor quarrel
between lovers.

34
00:02:21,625 --> 00:02:22,958
Only I can have one
with her.

35
00:02:23,041 --> 00:02:24,125
I'm the only one
she loves.

36
00:02:24,208 --> 00:02:25,333
The point?

37
00:02:25,416 --> 00:02:27,083
My show's in
our 'hood tomorrow.

38
00:02:27,166 --> 00:02:28,708
Industry people
will be there.

39
00:02:28,791 --> 00:02:30,708
Once they witness her
beauty, that's it.

40
00:02:30,791 --> 00:02:32,750
What will happen
if they scout her?

41
00:02:32,833 --> 00:02:33,666
[SAIKI]
Don't care.

42
00:02:33,750 --> 00:02:35,083
Won't be long
after her debut

43
00:02:35,166 --> 00:02:36,583
to land the lead
on her own TV show.

44
00:02:36,666 --> 00:02:38,666
Then she'll segue into
stage and movies roles,

45
00:02:38,750 --> 00:02:40,458
winning awards
and endorsement deals!

46
00:02:40,541 --> 00:02:41,833
[SAIKI]
I doubt it.

47
00:02:41,916 --> 00:02:43,541
[MUGAMI] Kokomi has
no interest in showbiz.

48
00:02:43,625 --> 00:02:45,583
[TERUHASHI] Flowers in
a flower shop are pretty.

49
00:02:45,666 --> 00:02:48,250
I'm a wildflower that
puts those flowers to shame!

50
00:02:48,333 --> 00:02:49,458
Which is why,
this once,

51
00:02:49,541 --> 00:02:51,083
you have permission
to speak to her

52
00:02:51,166 --> 00:02:52,583
and help her avoid
filming location.

53
00:02:52,666 --> 00:02:55,125
Don't say anything else,
don't make eye contact

54
00:02:55,208 --> 00:02:56,666
and don't get within
10 meters!

55
00:02:56,750 --> 00:02:57,625
[SAIKI]
Come on.

56
00:02:57,708 --> 00:02:59,166
I'd prefer
to tell her myself,

57
00:02:59,250 --> 00:03:00,416
but this lovers'
quarrel.

58
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:02,000
[chuckles]
Don't screw this up.

59
00:03:02,083 --> 00:03:04,375
[SAIKI] I don't wanna do this,
but it could be bad for me

60
00:03:04,458 --> 00:03:05,500
if she becomes a TV star.

61
00:03:05,583 --> 00:03:06,875
All her fans gathering
in front

62
00:03:06,958 --> 00:03:08,833
of the school every day,
getting in my way.

63
00:03:08,916 --> 00:03:11,291
What? He came to see you?
Aw, I'm sorry

64
00:03:11,375 --> 00:03:13,208
if my brother caused you
any trouble.

65
00:03:13,291 --> 00:03:14,625
[SAIKI]
That's putting it mildly.

66
00:03:14,708 --> 00:03:16,041
[TERUHASHI]
Why are you so far away?

67
00:03:16,125 --> 00:03:17,166
[SAIKI]
Ask your brother.

68
00:03:17,250 --> 00:03:18,625
I'm sorry.
Stupid brother!

69
00:03:18,708 --> 00:03:21,583
Causing trouble for Saiki!
Now I have to offer

70
00:03:21,666 --> 00:03:23,625
an apologetic gesture
to make it up to him.

71
00:03:23,708 --> 00:03:25,791
[SAIKI] Gave her his message.
Now I can go home.

72
00:03:25,875 --> 00:03:28,500
Wait, are you free
after school today?

73
00:03:28,583 --> 00:03:30,291
That's right!
I have to do this!

74
00:03:30,375 --> 00:03:31,791
Do you know how lucky
you are?

75
00:03:31,875 --> 00:03:35,000
I'm obligated to apologize
so my hands are tied.

76
00:03:35,083 --> 00:03:38,291
Would you like to grab
some tea after school?

77
00:03:38,375 --> 00:03:39,791
It'll be my treat!

78
00:03:39,875 --> 00:03:42,458
Feel honored! This is only
an obligatory gesture,

79
00:03:42,541 --> 00:03:44,791
I've never asked anyone
out on a date before!

80
00:03:44,875 --> 00:03:47,333
You might even say
your first, "oh, wow," huh?

81
00:03:47,416 --> 00:03:48,958
What? Oh, I get it.

82
00:03:49,041 --> 00:03:51,583
You're so moved by my offer
that you're speechless.

83
00:03:51,666 --> 00:03:53,416
That must be it,
'cause there's no way

84
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:54,833
any man could ever
turn me down!

85
00:03:54,916 --> 00:03:56,666
[SAIKI] Actually, I was
going to decline, but--

86
00:03:56,750 --> 00:03:58,458
[TERUHASHI] If I can't go
where they're filming,

87
00:03:58,541 --> 00:04:00,208
how 'bout we go
to a neighboring town?

88
00:04:00,291 --> 00:04:01,416
[heart beating]

89
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:02,875
If you reject me,
I'll just die!

90
00:04:02,958 --> 00:04:05,333
My life will officially be over!
Say, "Yes" already!

91
00:04:05,416 --> 00:04:06,875
[SAIKI]
Hard to say no to that.

92
00:04:06,958 --> 00:04:08,708
[TERUHASHI] A date with Saiki
in a neighboring town!

93
00:04:08,791 --> 00:04:11,416
It's not a date. Just a gesture.
My hands are tied.

94
00:04:11,500 --> 00:04:12,750
[MAN 1]
She's cute!

95
00:04:12,833 --> 00:04:14,500
[MAN 2] Never seen such
a girl here before.

96
00:04:14,583 --> 00:04:16,500
[TERUHASHI] He must be
experiencing bliss right now!

97
00:04:16,583 --> 00:04:18,541
He's been all smiles since
our date started!

98
00:04:18,625 --> 00:04:20,166
Bet I'll hear him say,
"Oh, wow,"

99
00:04:20,250 --> 00:04:21,500
at least
20 times today!

100
00:04:21,583 --> 00:04:23,208
[SAIKI] Seriously?
I thought it'd be okay

101
00:04:23,291 --> 00:04:24,708
since I don't know
anybody here.

102
00:04:24,791 --> 00:04:27,041
[MAN 1] What's she doing
with that guy?

103
00:04:27,125 --> 00:04:29,458
[SAIKI] I'll tell her I don't
feel well and go home--

104
00:04:29,541 --> 00:04:32,166
Do you like desserts,
Saiki? There's a café

105
00:04:32,250 --> 00:04:33,500
nearby that has delicious cakes.

106
00:04:33,583 --> 00:04:35,291
[SAIKI] --right after
I have some cake.

107
00:04:35,375 --> 00:04:36,666
[TERUHASHI]
Ha. I've done my research,

108
00:04:36,750 --> 00:04:38,416
so I know Saiki
has a sweet tooth.

109
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:40,750
An "oh, wow" festival's
about to begin!

110
00:04:42,291 --> 00:04:43,416
It's closed?

111
00:04:43,500 --> 00:04:44,916
It looks like
they're closed.

112
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:47,250
Let's check out
that district over there?

113
00:04:47,333 --> 00:04:49,083
We came all this way,
might as well

114
00:04:49,166 --> 00:04:50,375
get something to eat!

115
00:04:50,458 --> 00:04:52,166
There's nothing here.

116
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:55,291
How is there a shopping district
without a single restaurant?

117
00:04:55,375 --> 00:04:56,666
Three tatami mat stores
in a row?

118
00:04:56,750 --> 00:04:58,416
What is this,
the tatami mat district?

119
00:04:58,500 --> 00:05:00,000
Is that a café?

120
00:05:00,083 --> 00:05:01,208
Another tatami
store?

121
00:05:01,291 --> 00:05:02,625
[SAIKI] That cup
is misleading.

122
00:05:02,708 --> 00:05:04,708
Uh, 'scuse me.
Can I help with something?

123
00:05:04,791 --> 00:05:07,041
[TERUHASHI] We're looking for
somewhere to get tea.

124
00:05:07,125 --> 00:05:08,458
I know!
I saw her first!

125
00:05:08,541 --> 00:05:09,958
It's so sunny.
Take this.

126
00:05:10,041 --> 00:05:11,208
Here's a café
coupon!

127
00:05:11,291 --> 00:05:12,833
[BOY]
I'll reserve a table for you!

128
00:05:12,916 --> 00:05:14,000
Thank you so much.

129
00:05:14,083 --> 00:05:15,208
[CROWD]
Oh, wow!

130
00:05:15,291 --> 00:05:16,375
[TERUHASHI]
An "oh, wow" festival!

131
00:05:16,458 --> 00:05:17,375
More tea?

132
00:05:17,458 --> 00:05:18,625
I'm all good now,
so bye!

133
00:05:18,708 --> 00:05:20,250
Saiki made me forget
for a minute,

134
00:05:20,333 --> 00:05:23,041
but these guys reminded me
I'm the perfect pretty girl!

135
00:05:23,125 --> 00:05:24,375
Now back to our date!

136
00:05:24,458 --> 00:05:26,083
[SAIKI] Teruhashi really is
relentless.

137
00:05:26,166 --> 00:05:28,625
I'll just deal with this,
then hurry back home.

138
00:05:28,708 --> 00:05:30,583
I wonder if they're done
filming yet.

139
00:05:30,666 --> 00:05:32,458
[MAN]
Ugh! Can't believe the director

140
00:05:32,541 --> 00:05:34,333
switched locations
at the last minute.

141
00:05:34,416 --> 00:05:35,916
To the neighboring town,
right?

142
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,875
[MUGAMI] Guess I didn't need
to talk to him after all.

143
00:05:37,958 --> 00:05:40,250
[SAIKI] He's coming this way?
We gotta leave town.

144
00:05:40,333 --> 00:05:41,750
Soon as we finish our cake.

145
00:05:41,833 --> 00:05:43,708
♪

146
00:05:48,208 --> 00:05:49,500
[SAIKI]
This is bad.

147
00:05:49,583 --> 00:05:52,500
Teruhashi's brother
is headed right for us.

148
00:05:52,583 --> 00:05:54,583
If he runs into her,
he'll make a big fuss.

149
00:05:54,666 --> 00:05:57,416
What should I do?
This puts me in a real bind.

150
00:05:57,500 --> 00:05:58,833
I gotta do something.

151
00:05:58,916 --> 00:06:00,500
Should we order
any more cake?

152
00:06:00,583 --> 00:06:02,291
[SAIKI] I gotta do something
right after that.

153
00:06:02,375 --> 00:06:04,791
[TERUHASHI] Ah, that was so
delicious, wasn't it, Saiki?

154
00:06:04,875 --> 00:06:06,833
[SAIKI] What a pain.
We sure took our time here,

155
00:06:06,916 --> 00:06:08,708
even with her brother
approaching.

156
00:06:08,791 --> 00:06:10,750
This may be a small town,
but hopefully,

157
00:06:10,833 --> 00:06:12,458
it's big enough
we won't see him.

158
00:06:12,541 --> 00:06:14,708
That place looks popular.
Wanna pop in there?

159
00:06:14,791 --> 00:06:16,375
Yeah, if their food's
that good,

160
00:06:16,458 --> 00:06:17,833
I can bring Kokomi
sometime.

161
00:06:17,916 --> 00:06:19,791
[SAIKI] They're moving the plot
forward too quickly.

162
00:06:19,875 --> 00:06:21,500
We'd better
get out of here now.

163
00:06:21,583 --> 00:06:23,041
[TERUHASHI] You wanna leave
already? Can you wait?

164
00:06:23,125 --> 00:06:26,125
There's still a line of people
who want to shake my hand.

165
00:06:26,208 --> 00:06:29,250
[SAIKI] Now's not the time!
Damn it, I have no choice.

166
00:06:29,333 --> 00:06:31,041
Oh, no, it's closed?
Not open?

167
00:06:31,125 --> 00:06:33,750
There's a girl in there
shaking hands with people.

168
00:06:33,833 --> 00:06:35,291
I wonder if she's
a pop star.

169
00:06:35,375 --> 00:06:36,416
Why don't you sneak in?

170
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:37,833
They'd get
a kick out of it.

171
00:06:37,916 --> 00:06:39,833
[MUGAMI] I don't wanna ruin
the event for her.

172
00:06:39,916 --> 00:06:41,875
They'd all flock
to me and abandon her.

173
00:06:41,958 --> 00:06:43,958
[SAIKI] Actually, you'd wind up
standing in line.

174
00:06:44,041 --> 00:06:45,833
[MUGAMI]
Let's just go somewhere else.

175
00:06:45,916 --> 00:06:47,708
[SAIKI] Now's our chance
to sneak out of here.

176
00:06:47,791 --> 00:06:50,625
That'll be 6,850 yen.

177
00:06:50,708 --> 00:06:52,333
How much?
Oh, I'll be paying!

178
00:06:52,416 --> 00:06:53,625
How much
did you say it is?

179
00:06:53,708 --> 00:06:55,291
You are? In that case,
200 yen.

180
00:06:55,375 --> 00:06:57,333
That cheap?
I have some coupons, too!

181
00:06:57,416 --> 00:06:58,416
Then it's 20 yen.

182
00:06:58,500 --> 00:06:59,583
[SAIKI]
Hope in my next life

183
00:06:59,666 --> 00:07:00,916
I come back
as a pretty girl.

184
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:03,291
[TERUHASHI]
Wonder if they're done filming.

185
00:07:03,375 --> 00:07:04,541
It's probably safe
to go back,

186
00:07:04,625 --> 00:07:05,833
but we could always
hang out.

187
00:07:05,916 --> 00:07:07,250
[SAIKI]
We're going straight home.

188
00:07:07,333 --> 00:07:09,791
Huh? What's wrong with this guy?

189
00:07:09,875 --> 00:07:12,166
I'm giving off the "let's stay
a while longer" vibe

190
00:07:12,250 --> 00:07:14,708
yet he still can't wait
to board a train out of here?

191
00:07:14,791 --> 00:07:16,625
[SAIKI] Unfortunately,
we may have to wait.

192
00:07:16,708 --> 00:07:18,583
They're at
the train station!

193
00:07:18,666 --> 00:07:20,166
Great, we're stuck here.

194
00:07:20,250 --> 00:07:21,541
[TERUHASHI]
Huh? He stopped?

195
00:07:21,625 --> 00:07:22,958
He must be
feeling torn!

196
00:07:23,041 --> 00:07:25,041
[SAIKI] I wanna spend more time
with Teruhashi,

197
00:07:25,125 --> 00:07:26,875
but I don't have
the guts to say so!

198
00:07:26,958 --> 00:07:28,750
[TERUHASHI] That's why he
stopped in his tracks!

199
00:07:28,833 --> 00:07:30,791
Aw, what am I gonna do
with this shy boy?

200
00:07:30,875 --> 00:07:32,708
Guess I'll have to say
what he can't.

201
00:07:32,791 --> 00:07:36,166
Hey. If you wanna keep hanging
out for a while, we can.

202
00:07:36,250 --> 00:07:37,583
[SAIKI]
Our date drags on.

203
00:07:37,666 --> 00:07:39,541
[TERUHASHI] I haven't been
to a place like this

204
00:07:39,625 --> 00:07:41,041
in forever!
So many choices!

205
00:07:41,125 --> 00:07:42,958
[SAIKI] This might actually
work out for the best,

206
00:07:43,041 --> 00:07:44,791
in terms of making
Teruhashi hate me.

207
00:07:44,875 --> 00:07:46,666
Oh, they have
karaoke!

208
00:07:46,750 --> 00:07:48,000
Hope he takes
the hint.

209
00:07:48,083 --> 00:07:49,708
I'd much rather sing
than go bowling.

210
00:07:49,791 --> 00:07:51,916
[MAN] Two for bowling, right?
[TERUHASHI] What?

211
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:54,708
[SAIKI] I do feel kind of bad,
but it's better this way.

212
00:07:54,791 --> 00:07:57,041
[TERUHASHI] He could've asked me
before deciding to bowl.

213
00:07:57,125 --> 00:07:59,833
I bet he wanted to impress
me by showing off his coolness!

214
00:07:59,916 --> 00:08:01,416
That's why he picked
bowling!

215
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:03,291
This is Saiki,
so there's a chance

216
00:08:03,375 --> 00:08:04,875
he'll get nervous
and screw-up.

217
00:08:04,958 --> 00:08:07,083
At least then
we'll be evenly matched.

218
00:08:07,166 --> 00:08:08,416
[pins rattling]
Aah!

219
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:09,750
[SAIKI]
I humiliated her.

220
00:08:09,833 --> 00:08:11,541
Bet she likes me
a lot less now.

221
00:08:11,625 --> 00:08:14,583
[TERUHASHI] Look! They've got
Gori-rabbitz stuffed animals!

222
00:08:14,666 --> 00:08:16,041
Saiki, are you
any good at--

223
00:08:16,125 --> 00:08:17,750
[SAIKI] Eh, I'll do
this one instead.

224
00:08:17,833 --> 00:08:19,666
I know how much
you hate these figures,

225
00:08:19,750 --> 00:08:21,166
so I'll grab
the worst one.

226
00:08:21,250 --> 00:08:22,666
What?
And next,

227
00:08:22,750 --> 00:08:24,041
I'll--
[thudding]

228
00:08:25,833 --> 00:08:27,875
[TERUHASHI] So this is what
he's really like.

229
00:08:27,958 --> 00:08:30,750
[SAIKI] Teruhashi must've lost
interest in me by now.

230
00:08:30,833 --> 00:08:32,333
[TERUHASHI]
Should we go home now?

231
00:08:32,416 --> 00:08:33,875
[SAIKI]
If that's what you want.

232
00:08:33,958 --> 00:08:35,458
[MUGAMI] Whoa, I'm exhausted.
[SAIKI] What?

233
00:08:35,541 --> 00:08:37,250
Shoot! There are
so many people around

234
00:08:37,333 --> 00:08:39,916
and I was so focused on
Teruhashi's inner thoughts

235
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:43,083
that I didn't even notice him!
We gotta get out of here fast!

236
00:08:43,166 --> 00:08:44,583
Is that you, four-eyes?

237
00:08:44,666 --> 00:08:46,250
Time's up.
What? Kokomi?

238
00:08:46,333 --> 00:08:47,625
[SAIKI]
It'll be okay.

239
00:08:47,708 --> 00:08:49,291
He and I still share
the same goal.

240
00:08:49,375 --> 00:08:51,833
[MUGAMI] Since I said we'd be
filming in our neighborhood,

241
00:08:51,916 --> 00:08:54,500
she must've come here
to get away...with four-eyes.

242
00:08:54,583 --> 00:08:55,958
Sneaky, rotten four-eyes!

243
00:08:56,041 --> 00:08:58,541
Using that as an excuse
to go out with my Kokomi?

244
00:08:58,625 --> 00:09:00,958
[SAIKI]
Don't lose sight of our goal.

245
00:09:01,041 --> 00:09:02,333
What's wrong?
[groans]

246
00:09:02,416 --> 00:09:04,041
[SAIKI]
Oh crap! We gotta go now!

247
00:09:04,125 --> 00:09:05,625
Huh?

248
00:09:05,708 --> 00:09:07,958
That four-eyed bastard
just grabbed her hand!

249
00:09:08,041 --> 00:09:09,750
Don't let him get away!
After him!

250
00:09:09,833 --> 00:09:12,208
[SAIKI] One minute.
Just have to buy us one minute.

251
00:09:12,291 --> 00:09:15,625
We got him! Huh! Not in here.
Where'd he go?

252
00:09:15,708 --> 00:09:17,083
[SAIKI]
That was close.

253
00:09:17,166 --> 00:09:18,958
Had to make both of us
invisible.

254
00:09:19,041 --> 00:09:20,791
If I'm touching
someone else,

255
00:09:20,875 --> 00:09:22,916
I can hide them
right along with me.

256
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,291
[TERUHASHI]
The nerve of him!

257
00:09:24,375 --> 00:09:25,791
I can't believe
he took my hand!

258
00:09:25,875 --> 00:09:27,125
What's gotten into
that boy?

259
00:09:27,208 --> 00:09:28,708
[SAIKI] I bet she hates me
even more

260
00:09:28,791 --> 00:09:30,541
now that I grabbed her
without permission.

261
00:09:30,625 --> 00:09:32,958
[TERUHASHI] What an arrogant,
aggressive, entitled jerk!

262
00:09:33,041 --> 00:09:35,166
[SAIKI] I guess it's for the
best. Now she'll finally be--

263
00:09:35,250 --> 00:09:38,916
[TERUHASHI] But why? Why is my
heart fluttering like crazy?

264
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:40,291
[sighs]

265
00:09:40,375 --> 00:09:41,583
♪

266
00:09:41,666 --> 00:09:43,458
We gonna take a pic?

267
00:09:43,541 --> 00:09:45,333
[SAIKI]
Well, that's a twist.

268
00:09:45,416 --> 00:09:46,625
[shutter clicks]

269
00:09:46,708 --> 00:09:47,666
♪ C'mon! ♪

270
00:09:47,750 --> 00:09:48,833
[SAIKI]
Use telepathy to win

271
00:09:48,916 --> 00:09:50,875
the rock-paper-
scissors game!

272
00:09:52,333 --> 00:09:54,208
♪

273
00:09:56,750 --> 00:09:58,625
[TAKU]
There's no such thing as Santa!

274
00:09:58,708 --> 00:10:00,500
Don't be silly,
of course there is!

275
00:10:00,583 --> 00:10:02,500
She's right, Taku,
Santa's very real!

276
00:10:02,583 --> 00:10:03,541
[TAKU]
Ken said he's not.

277
00:10:03,625 --> 00:10:04,750
[doorbell rings]

278
00:10:04,833 --> 00:10:06,416
Sounds like
we've got a visitor.

279
00:10:06,500 --> 00:10:07,666
Maybe it's Santa Claus.

280
00:10:07,750 --> 00:10:09,958
Bet it's just
a delivery guy.

281
00:10:10,041 --> 00:10:11,333
[door opens]

282
00:10:11,416 --> 00:10:12,708
[bell jingles]
Huh?

283
00:10:12,791 --> 00:10:14,708
Whoa! Santa Claus?

284
00:10:14,791 --> 00:10:16,666
Yeah right, as if
I'd react like that.

285
00:10:16,750 --> 00:10:18,250
My parents
put you up to this?

286
00:10:18,333 --> 00:10:19,375
Nice effort,
dude.

287
00:10:19,458 --> 00:10:20,625
Can I have
my present now?

288
00:10:20,708 --> 00:10:22,625
[SAIKI]
Cheeky little brat.

289
00:10:22,708 --> 00:10:24,750
He disappeared!

290
00:10:24,833 --> 00:10:26,666
Mom! That was Santa!
He's real!

291
00:10:26,750 --> 00:10:27,916
[SAIKI]
What a pain.

292
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:30,666
How'd I get myself
into this?

293
00:10:30,750 --> 00:10:32,875
[KUNIHARO]
Hello, Kusuo, I'm Santa Claus!

294
00:10:32,958 --> 00:10:34,083
I'm delivering
presents

295
00:10:34,166 --> 00:10:36,000
to the children
in the neighborhood.

296
00:10:36,083 --> 00:10:37,833
[SAIKI] So you've
finally cracked, Dad?

297
00:10:37,916 --> 00:10:39,375
[KURUMI] I told the neighbors
about how your dad

298
00:10:39,458 --> 00:10:41,250
dresses up as Santa every year
and they asked

299
00:10:41,333 --> 00:10:42,875
if he could come
to their houses, too.

300
00:10:42,958 --> 00:10:44,375
[SAIKI]
Don't spread our shame.

301
00:10:44,458 --> 00:10:47,083
Everybody's waiting on a visit
from Kuniharu Claus!

302
00:10:47,166 --> 00:10:48,541
[SAIKI]
You're a lost Claus.

303
00:10:48,625 --> 00:10:50,583
Well, I'm off now!
See ya! Ahh--!

304
00:10:50,666 --> 00:10:52,666
Honey, what's wrong?
[KUNIHARU] My back!

305
00:10:52,750 --> 00:10:54,416
It's my back.
I did it. I did it.

306
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:56,708
I really did it this time.
Aah-aah! I did it.

307
00:10:56,791 --> 00:10:58,500
[SAIKI]
Enough with the "I did it."

308
00:10:58,583 --> 00:10:59,791
[KUNIHARU]
Please, fix this, Kusuo.

309
00:10:59,875 --> 00:11:01,416
[SAIKI]
Guess I have to. Wait, I can't.

310
00:11:01,500 --> 00:11:04,083
I already turned back time
on you this morning.

311
00:11:04,166 --> 00:11:07,666
[KUNIHARU] I stubbed my pinky
toe! Kusuo-mon, help! Yay.

312
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:09,458
Oh, no! Kusuo,
you have to deliver

313
00:11:09,541 --> 00:11:11,041
these presents for me!
No way.

314
00:11:11,125 --> 00:11:13,166
Please, I'm begging you,
Santa Kusuo!

315
00:11:13,250 --> 00:11:14,916
[SAIKI] Don't ever
call me that again.

316
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:18,083
I'll do it!
Just leave it to me, all right!

317
00:11:18,166 --> 00:11:19,916
[silence]

318
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:21,291
[SAIKI] So that's how
I wound up here.

319
00:11:21,375 --> 00:11:23,250
As a son, it's my duty
to stop my mother

320
00:11:23,333 --> 00:11:25,416
from walking around
our neighborhood

321
00:11:25,500 --> 00:11:26,750
in a sexy Santa
costume.

322
00:11:26,833 --> 00:11:28,458
I just wanna get this
over with quickly.

323
00:11:28,541 --> 00:11:31,416
It'll go faster if I fly through
the sky like the real Santa.

324
00:11:31,500 --> 00:11:34,291
There's the next house
on my list. What a pain.

325
00:11:34,375 --> 00:11:36,458
[GIRL]
Dad, will Santa be here soon?

326
00:11:36,541 --> 00:11:37,791
Yes, of course,
very soon.

327
00:11:37,875 --> 00:11:39,041
Goody!
When he comes,

328
00:11:39,125 --> 00:11:40,500
I'm gonna ask him
to give me a hug!

329
00:11:40,583 --> 00:11:42,458
[SAIKI] If it's for a kid,
I have no choice.

330
00:11:42,541 --> 00:11:45,583
When he gets here, Santa's
coming down the chimney, right?

331
00:11:45,666 --> 00:11:47,458
[FATHER]
Hm, I don't know about that.

332
00:11:47,541 --> 00:11:48,791
[GIRL]
Of course he will!

333
00:11:48,875 --> 00:11:50,708
He wouldn't walk up
and ring the doorbell.

334
00:11:50,791 --> 00:11:52,208
[MOTHER]
The chimney's dangerous.

335
00:11:52,291 --> 00:11:53,791
[GIRL]
Not for Santa! If he comes

336
00:11:53,875 --> 00:11:55,791
through the door,
I'll be disillusioned.

337
00:11:55,875 --> 00:11:57,083
[FATHER]
"Disillusioned"?

338
00:11:57,166 --> 00:11:58,666
Where'd you learn
that word?

339
00:11:58,750 --> 00:12:00,250
[loud crash]
Aah!

340
00:12:00,333 --> 00:12:03,000
Santa's here?
Santa's here!

341
00:12:04,750 --> 00:12:06,125
Uh...
[SAIKI] Don't look so

342
00:12:06,208 --> 00:12:08,083
disillusioned, kid.
Here's your presen--

343
00:12:08,166 --> 00:12:09,791
[GIRL] Please leave it
under the tree and go.

344
00:12:09,875 --> 00:12:11,166
[SAIKI]
Another brat.

345
00:12:11,250 --> 00:12:12,916
Weren't you going
to ask for a hug?

346
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:14,291
I'm afraid
I'll have to decline.

347
00:12:14,375 --> 00:12:16,166
But I appreciate
all your efforts, sir.

348
00:12:16,250 --> 00:12:17,833
[SAIKI]
Cut the polite talk.

349
00:12:17,916 --> 00:12:20,083
Seriously.
What a bunch of lousy kids.

350
00:12:20,166 --> 00:12:21,833
At least there's no chimney
this time.

351
00:12:21,916 --> 00:12:23,000
[doorbell rings]

352
00:12:23,083 --> 00:12:24,666
Hello, sir.
What do you want?

353
00:12:24,750 --> 00:12:26,125
Do you mind if I ask
who you are?

354
00:12:26,208 --> 00:12:28,000
[SAIKI] Oh, come on.
You must know Santa?

355
00:12:28,083 --> 00:12:30,541
[BOY] My mom's not home!
So please, just go away!

356
00:12:30,625 --> 00:12:33,625
[SAIKI] Don't you recognize me?
I'm Santa, killer.

357
00:12:33,708 --> 00:12:35,416
Hold on,
what'd you just say?

358
00:12:35,500 --> 00:12:37,000
You're a Santa killer?

359
00:12:37,083 --> 00:12:39,000
[SAIKI]
I was calling you "killer"!

360
00:12:39,083 --> 00:12:41,125
You don't want me!
I'm Kanta, not Santa!

361
00:12:41,208 --> 00:12:42,416
[SAIKI]
Close enough.

362
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:44,083
[screaming]

363
00:12:45,875 --> 00:12:47,750
[SAIKI] Parents, teach your kids
about Santa.

364
00:12:47,833 --> 00:12:49,333
At least tell him
I'm coming.

365
00:12:49,416 --> 00:12:50,500
The last house.

366
00:12:50,583 --> 00:12:52,708
After this I can go home
and eat some cake.

367
00:12:52,791 --> 00:12:54,666
[WOMAN]
You're going to the office now?

368
00:12:54,750 --> 00:12:56,291
[MAN]
They said it couldn't wait!

369
00:12:56,375 --> 00:12:59,083
What about the party? Kenta's
been looking forward to it!

370
00:12:59,166 --> 00:13:00,291
[MAN]
I have to go!

371
00:13:00,375 --> 00:13:02,083
[SAIKI] This seems like
a bad time.

372
00:13:02,166 --> 00:13:04,625
I'm just gonna leave
the present by the door and go.

373
00:13:04,708 --> 00:13:05,791
[BOY]
Dearest Santa,

374
00:13:05,875 --> 00:13:07,375
I don't need any presents.

375
00:13:07,458 --> 00:13:09,958
Please, just make
Mom and Dad stop fighting

376
00:13:10,041 --> 00:13:12,375
so we can have our
Christmas party together.

377
00:13:12,458 --> 00:13:15,625
Oh, Santa, please do that
for me. Please, Santa.

378
00:13:15,708 --> 00:13:17,625
[SAIKI]
That's not how it works.

379
00:13:17,708 --> 00:13:19,333
You're praying
to Santa Claus?

380
00:13:19,416 --> 00:13:21,208
He's not God
or Buddha, you know.

381
00:13:21,291 --> 00:13:23,875
You shouldn't expect
too much from a guy

382
00:13:23,958 --> 00:13:25,750
who takes
364 days off a year.

383
00:13:25,833 --> 00:13:28,750
Ugh! Seriously.
What a pain.

384
00:13:31,125 --> 00:13:33,083
I have to go now
but I'll make it up to you!

385
00:13:33,166 --> 00:13:34,625
Ugh, I can't
believe you!

386
00:13:34,708 --> 00:13:35,875
[phone rings]
What?

387
00:13:35,958 --> 00:13:37,708
Everything's been
taken care of?

388
00:13:37,791 --> 00:13:39,000
Wait, what?
Slow down.

389
00:13:39,083 --> 00:13:40,666
Santa Claus showed up
and did it all?

390
00:13:40,750 --> 00:13:43,541
Mom, Dad! Look what I found!
Santa left it for me!

391
00:13:43,625 --> 00:13:47,333
And he helped you out, too, Dad,
so you could stay here with us!

392
00:13:47,416 --> 00:13:49,125
Thank you, Santa Claus!

393
00:13:49,208 --> 00:13:51,458
[SAIKI] Man, that was
a lot of work.

394
00:13:52,666 --> 00:13:55,875
No wonder Santa has to take
364 days off.

395
00:13:56,791 --> 00:13:58,875
♪

396
00:14:01,791 --> 00:14:03,583
[KURUMI]
Happy New Year!

397
00:14:03,666 --> 00:14:04,875
Here's your gift
money.

398
00:14:04,958 --> 00:14:06,250
Be a good boy
again this year.

399
00:14:06,333 --> 00:14:08,041
Here you go.
This is from me.

400
00:14:08,125 --> 00:14:10,208
Spend it wisely,
okay? Huh?

401
00:14:10,291 --> 00:14:11,416
[squeaks]

402
00:14:11,500 --> 00:14:13,583
I'm sure I gave you
as much as your mom did.

403
00:14:13,666 --> 00:14:15,125
[SAIKI] Santa.
[KUNIHARU] What?

404
00:14:15,208 --> 00:14:17,041
[SAIKI] You were late for work.
[KUNIHARU] Yeah, but--

405
00:14:17,125 --> 00:14:18,916
[SAIKI] You spilled coffee
on that author's work.

406
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:20,375
[KUNIHARU] All right, Kuu,
let's talk this out!

407
00:14:20,458 --> 00:14:22,250
[Kuniharu weeping]
[SAIKI] This is enough.

408
00:14:22,333 --> 00:14:23,791
Well, guess I'll be
going now.

409
00:14:23,875 --> 00:14:26,125
What I'm looking to buy
is a new TV.

410
00:14:26,208 --> 00:14:28,750
Three years ago, the one
in my room stopped working.

411
00:14:28,833 --> 00:14:30,041
Since then,
I've had to keep

412
00:14:30,125 --> 00:14:31,625
turning back time on it
every day.

413
00:14:31,708 --> 00:14:34,333
That means it's always just
one day away from dying.

414
00:14:34,416 --> 00:14:37,083
So I think it's about time for
both me and the TV to move on.

415
00:14:37,166 --> 00:14:38,375
Looking for a TV?

416
00:14:38,458 --> 00:14:40,208
[SAIKI] Leave me alone.
I don't need help.

417
00:14:40,291 --> 00:14:42,375
Good choice, sir.
This one's very popular.

418
00:14:42,458 --> 00:14:44,166
[SAIKI] Great,
he's the pushy type.

419
00:14:44,250 --> 00:14:46,500
[NAKAMARU] This one's so light
you can carry it anywhere.

420
00:14:46,583 --> 00:14:48,833
[SAIKI] Doesn't matter to me.
I was carrying around

421
00:14:48,916 --> 00:14:50,083
a tube TV
when I was a baby.

422
00:14:50,166 --> 00:14:52,041
Please,
just leave me alone.

423
00:14:52,125 --> 00:14:53,750
[NAKAMARU] I bet he's got
some gift money to spend.

424
00:14:53,833 --> 00:14:56,791
I'll show him what four months
of sales experience can do!

425
00:14:56,875 --> 00:14:58,541
[SAIKI]
What? He's a total rookie!

426
00:14:58,625 --> 00:15:00,041
What about
this beauty?

427
00:15:00,125 --> 00:15:01,958
It's recommended
on <i>Nerdy Comedians!</i>

428
00:15:02,041 --> 00:15:04,166
Just look at that crisp
ultra-high-def image!

429
00:15:04,250 --> 00:15:05,500
[SAIKI]
That does sound impressive,

430
00:15:05,583 --> 00:15:07,333
but after looking at it
for two seconds,

431
00:15:07,416 --> 00:15:09,166
I can see inside.
The wiring's a mess,

432
00:15:09,250 --> 00:15:11,125
which doesn't bode well
for its quality.

433
00:15:11,208 --> 00:15:13,875
This model has a built-in
one-terabyte hard drive DVR

434
00:15:13,958 --> 00:15:15,750
that can store
hours of recordings.

435
00:15:15,833 --> 00:15:16,833
[SAIKI]
I don't record.

436
00:15:16,916 --> 00:15:18,000
If I miss a show

437
00:15:18,083 --> 00:15:19,333
I get it via
telepathy.

438
00:15:19,416 --> 00:15:21,041
If you connect it
to the Internet,

439
00:15:21,125 --> 00:15:22,541
you can see comments
in real time!

440
00:15:22,625 --> 00:15:24,333
[SAIKI] That feature
comes standard with me.

441
00:15:24,416 --> 00:15:26,291
But wait, there's more!
Believe it or not,

442
00:15:26,375 --> 00:15:27,666
this model offers
3D viewing!

443
00:15:27,750 --> 00:15:29,333
[SAIKI] No, thanks.
Reminds me of the time

444
00:15:29,416 --> 00:15:31,125
Nendou's dad
came through my screen.

445
00:15:31,208 --> 00:15:32,708
[NAKAMARU]
He's showing no interest!

446
00:15:32,791 --> 00:15:33,916
[SAIKI]
Man, what a pain.

447
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:35,666
Fine, I'll take
this one.

448
00:15:35,750 --> 00:15:38,166
[NAKAMARU] That one's not
recommended by <i>Nerdy Comedians.</i>

449
00:15:38,250 --> 00:15:40,500
[SAIKI]
I don't care! Gimme a discount.

450
00:15:40,583 --> 00:15:42,500
All right, tell you what,
I'll round it down

451
00:15:42,583 --> 00:15:44,708
to 49,000 yen,
plus double points,

452
00:15:44,791 --> 00:15:46,291
an alarm clock,
and 20 batter--

453
00:15:46,375 --> 00:15:47,500
What?
That's ridiculous!

454
00:15:47,583 --> 00:15:49,416
Are you trying to put us
out of business?

455
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:51,666
[SAIKI] It's not. It's the price
you thought of earlier.

456
00:15:51,750 --> 00:15:53,208
[NAKAMARU] I can go as low as
25,000 yen,

457
00:15:53,291 --> 00:15:54,541
but this brat doesn't
know.

458
00:15:54,625 --> 00:15:56,833
If I give him batteries,
he'll go home happy.

459
00:15:56,916 --> 00:15:58,625
[SAIKI]
No batteries, just the discount.

460
00:15:58,708 --> 00:16:01,125
[NAKAMARU] Damn it! He must've
checked out our prices online!

461
00:16:01,208 --> 00:16:03,625
You may have seen our
price match policy advertised,

462
00:16:03,708 --> 00:16:05,625
but I'm afraid
it only applies to stores

463
00:16:05,708 --> 00:16:08,125
with actual physical
locations, not websites.

464
00:16:08,208 --> 00:16:10,041
[SAIKI] I'll search all
the stores I've been to

465
00:16:10,125 --> 00:16:11,375
and create
a thoughtograph

466
00:16:11,458 --> 00:16:13,083
of the one
with the lowest price.

467
00:16:13,166 --> 00:16:16,541
This'll work!
26,700 in Gunma?

468
00:16:16,625 --> 00:16:18,666
[SAIKI] Feel free to call 'em
if you want.

469
00:16:18,750 --> 00:16:20,875
[NAKAMARU] Oh, fine,
that'll be 26,699 yen.

470
00:16:20,958 --> 00:16:22,208
[SAIKI]
Round down.

471
00:16:22,291 --> 00:16:23,750
[NAKAMARU]
I guess 26,000 is all right.

472
00:16:23,833 --> 00:16:25,250
[SAIKI]
Okay, let's check out.

473
00:16:25,333 --> 00:16:27,125
[NAKAMARU] This is the biggest
discount I've given

474
00:16:27,208 --> 00:16:30,083
since that unibrowed cop
while I was training in Kameari!

475
00:16:30,166 --> 00:16:31,541
But it's not over yet!

476
00:16:31,625 --> 00:16:34,250
I'll show you what
this 4-month veteran can do!

477
00:16:34,333 --> 00:16:35,916
While you're here,
can I interest you

478
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:37,125
in anything
besides the TV?

479
00:16:37,208 --> 00:16:38,416
[SAIKI]
I just wanna pay.

480
00:16:38,500 --> 00:16:40,166
Need noise-canceling
headphones?

481
00:16:40,250 --> 00:16:42,208
Create your own
quiet space wherever you go!

482
00:16:42,291 --> 00:16:43,791
They shut out
unwanted sounds

483
00:16:43,875 --> 00:16:45,083
so you can really
focus on--

484
00:16:45,166 --> 00:16:46,541
Buy 'em! Buy 'em!
Buy six pairs!

485
00:16:46,625 --> 00:16:48,125
[SAIKI]
His inner thoughts are louder

486
00:16:48,208 --> 00:16:49,375
than his outer ones.

487
00:16:49,458 --> 00:16:50,833
Or an electronic
dictionary

488
00:16:50,916 --> 00:16:52,083
to help with your
studies?

489
00:16:52,166 --> 00:16:53,416
[SAIKI]
I have everything in my head.

490
00:16:53,500 --> 00:16:55,666
A single-lens reflex
camera!

491
00:16:55,750 --> 00:16:57,958
[SAIKI] I can photograph
any place in the world

492
00:16:58,041 --> 00:16:59,333
via thoughtography.

493
00:16:59,416 --> 00:17:01,916
Fun gorilla MP3 player toy
hits the barrel

494
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:03,875
to the rhythm
of your music!

495
00:17:03,958 --> 00:17:05,583
[SAIKI]
Who would want a weird gorilla?

496
00:17:05,666 --> 00:17:08,000
Ahh! Can that make
coffee jelly?

497
00:17:08,083 --> 00:17:09,541
Jackpot! Good eyes, sir!

498
00:17:09,625 --> 00:17:11,750
We're the only store
that carries this machine.

499
00:17:11,833 --> 00:17:14,291
Just add water and you
can make all sorts of jellies,

500
00:17:14,375 --> 00:17:15,666
one click of
a button!

501
00:17:15,750 --> 00:17:17,125
[SAIKI]
Just one click?

502
00:17:17,208 --> 00:17:19,458
You can use the attachment
to make whipped cream.

503
00:17:19,541 --> 00:17:20,958
[SAIKI]
Whipped cream, too?

504
00:17:21,041 --> 00:17:22,958
It comes with a set
of cookie cutters

505
00:17:23,041 --> 00:17:24,291
in seven
fun shapes, too!

506
00:17:24,375 --> 00:17:25,500
[SAIKI]
Seven shapes?

507
00:17:25,583 --> 00:17:27,208
Did I mention
that it has a handle

508
00:17:27,291 --> 00:17:28,541
--for easy carrying?
--[SAIKI] A handle?

509
00:17:28,625 --> 00:17:30,291
He's like a different
person now!

510
00:17:30,375 --> 00:17:32,250
It runs on batteries
so you can use it anywhere

511
00:17:32,333 --> 00:17:33,875
all for this low,
low price!

512
00:17:33,958 --> 00:17:36,250
[SAIKI] If I buy the jelly-
maker, I won't afford the TV.

513
00:17:36,333 --> 00:17:37,625
I can only get one.
Problem is,

514
00:17:37,708 --> 00:17:39,791
if I oversleep even once
and don't fix my old TV,

515
00:17:39,875 --> 00:17:42,375
it'll never work again.
And if I make coffee jelly,

516
00:17:42,458 --> 00:17:44,250
I'll have to wash dishes
and clean up.

517
00:17:44,333 --> 00:17:45,541
Plus,
I'll need batteries.

518
00:17:45,625 --> 00:17:47,083
I should get the TV
after all.

519
00:17:47,166 --> 00:17:48,291
If you buy
the jelly-maker,

520
00:17:48,375 --> 00:17:49,875
you'll get double points,
a clock,

521
00:17:49,958 --> 00:17:52,416
dish detergent, table cleaner,
and 40 batteries!

522
00:17:52,500 --> 00:17:54,708
Does that sound good?
[SAIKI] Sold!

523
00:17:56,750 --> 00:17:59,291
Kuu, what'd you buy
with all your gift money?

524
00:17:59,375 --> 00:18:01,791
[SAIKI] Heh, heh. I should let
Mom have some, too.

525
00:18:01,875 --> 00:18:02,833
♪ C'mon! ♪

526
00:18:02,916 --> 00:18:04,541
Beat Hairo.
[HAIRO] 1-2-3!

527
00:18:04,625 --> 00:18:06,791
[SAIKI] He had rock
from the start.

528
00:18:06,875 --> 00:18:08,750
♪

529
00:18:11,666 --> 00:18:14,250
[Kaidou coughing]
[NENDOU] Droppin' a beat?

530
00:18:14,333 --> 00:18:15,958
Come down with
a cold, Kaidou?

531
00:18:16,041 --> 00:18:17,000
[KAIDOU]
Kind of.

532
00:18:17,083 --> 00:18:18,166
[SAIKI]
If you're sick,

533
00:18:18,250 --> 00:18:19,583
go to the hospital,
not school.

534
00:18:19,666 --> 00:18:21,458
This is the new
biological weapon

535
00:18:21,541 --> 00:18:23,250
that Dark Reunion
has unleashed

536
00:18:23,333 --> 00:18:25,333
as part of the first stage
of their plot

537
00:18:25,416 --> 00:18:26,541
to destroy the world!

538
00:18:26,625 --> 00:18:28,166
[SAIKI]
Just go to a doctor.

539
00:18:28,250 --> 00:18:29,625
Jeez, runt,
you're so weak.

540
00:18:29,708 --> 00:18:31,708
Come on! Everybody
catches colds!

541
00:18:31,791 --> 00:18:32,750
[SAIKI]
So it is a cold.

542
00:18:32,833 --> 00:18:34,666
Though not everybody
catches colds.

543
00:18:34,750 --> 00:18:36,625
I never have.
'Cause of my powers.

544
00:18:36,708 --> 00:18:37,833
I never caught one.

545
00:18:37,916 --> 00:18:39,041
Neither have I.

546
00:18:39,125 --> 00:18:40,583
[SAIKI]
That's not normal.

547
00:18:40,666 --> 00:18:42,916
[gasps]
Kuboyasu has a cold too?

548
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:44,125
--Huh?
--[KAIDOU] Your mask!

549
00:18:44,208 --> 00:18:45,375
Oh, right.

550
00:18:45,458 --> 00:18:47,125
[coughs]
See? Everybo--

551
00:18:47,208 --> 00:18:49,166
Everybody's so weak!
Not like me!

552
00:18:49,250 --> 00:18:50,875
[KUBOYASU] Oh, goody goodies
wear facemasks

553
00:18:50,958 --> 00:18:52,291
when they catch
a cold!

554
00:18:52,375 --> 00:18:54,250
[SAIKI] For punks,
it's a fashion statement.

555
00:18:55,458 --> 00:18:56,583
You serious? Hah!

556
00:18:56,666 --> 00:18:58,541
That's my first laugh
of the year!

557
00:18:58,625 --> 00:18:59,625
Huh?

558
00:18:59,708 --> 00:19:00,833
Hey, buddy! Runt!

559
00:19:00,916 --> 00:19:02,541
My first crazy dance move
of the year!

560
00:19:02,625 --> 00:19:04,041
[SAIKI]
My first "don't care."

561
00:19:04,125 --> 00:19:05,208
First weird face!

562
00:19:05,291 --> 00:19:07,000
[SAIKI]
Your face is always weird.

563
00:19:07,083 --> 00:19:08,583
Quit fooling around
you dumb jerk!

564
00:19:08,666 --> 00:19:10,416
Take my first
Ultimate Knight Storm!

565
00:19:10,500 --> 00:19:12,375
[NENDOU] Mera, that your
first ramen of the year?

566
00:19:12,458 --> 00:19:15,541
[MERA] First meal of the year.
I finally got paid today.

567
00:19:15,625 --> 00:19:17,416
I was mostly living
on grass and snow.

568
00:19:17,500 --> 00:19:19,083
I thought I was
gonna die.

569
00:19:19,166 --> 00:19:21,625
[SAIKI] Um, we're twenty days
into the new year all ready.

570
00:19:22,958 --> 00:19:25,083
What were you doin' at
the start of the new year?

571
00:19:25,166 --> 00:19:26,541
Why are you
asking that now?

572
00:19:26,625 --> 00:19:29,083
[TAKAHASHI] I wasn't on Earth
when at midnight!

573
00:19:29,166 --> 00:19:30,833
[YOKOTA]
Amazing, Takahashi!

574
00:19:30,916 --> 00:19:33,458
Amazing that you'd brag about
something so stupid.

575
00:19:33,541 --> 00:19:35,791
[TAKAHASHI]
You guys must've done that once!

576
00:19:35,875 --> 00:19:37,666
[SAIKI]
I tried it when I was little,

577
00:19:37,750 --> 00:19:39,541
but it really wasn't
much fun for me.

578
00:19:39,625 --> 00:19:41,833
All I could think
to say was,

579
00:19:41,916 --> 00:19:43,250
"the Earth is blue."

580
00:19:43,333 --> 00:19:44,916
What were you doing?

581
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:46,041
[SAIKI]
What, you, too?

582
00:19:46,125 --> 00:19:47,250
If you wanna leave Earth,

583
00:19:47,333 --> 00:19:48,750
I'll do whatever
I can to help.

584
00:19:48,833 --> 00:19:50,916
I was ringing the bell
at the temple.

585
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:52,291
You ring it
108 times

586
00:19:52,375 --> 00:19:54,000
to remove your 108
earthly desires, right?

587
00:19:54,083 --> 00:19:55,541
Sounds perfect
for you.

588
00:19:55,625 --> 00:19:57,208
[TORITSUKA] Yeah, but after
seven or eight times,

589
00:19:57,291 --> 00:19:58,208
my hands hurt,
so I quit.

590
00:19:58,291 --> 00:19:59,708
[SAIKI]
Earthly desire.

591
00:19:59,791 --> 00:20:01,458
[TORITSUKA] Then people came
and wanted to ring it,

592
00:20:01,541 --> 00:20:03,208
so I joked that it'd be
1000 yen per ring.

593
00:20:03,291 --> 00:20:04,875
And they paid!
I made a killing!

594
00:20:04,958 --> 00:20:05,916
[SAIKI]
Earthly desire.

595
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:07,375
This one girl
had huge knockers!

596
00:20:07,458 --> 00:20:09,750
Every time she rang the bell,
they bounced like crazy!

597
00:20:09,833 --> 00:20:11,958
The New Year's Eve bell
is the absolute best!

598
00:20:12,041 --> 00:20:14,833
[SAIKI] Earthly desire. Next
time, hit your head 108 times.

599
00:20:18,125 --> 00:20:19,375
♪

600
00:20:19,458 --> 00:20:21,750
I gained weight.
Oh, no! This is very bad!

601
00:20:21,833 --> 00:20:23,500
I know I ate a lot
over the holidays,

602
00:20:23,583 --> 00:20:25,291
but how'd I gain
so much?

603
00:20:25,375 --> 00:20:26,833
Look at the ugly
piggy.

604
00:20:26,916 --> 00:20:29,291
[YUMEHARA] Kaidou will be
disgusted! What should I do?

605
00:20:29,375 --> 00:20:30,625
Right!
The bath towel!

606
00:20:30,708 --> 00:20:33,291
That's gotta weigh at least
five kilograms.

607
00:20:34,875 --> 00:20:35,791
[beeps]

608
00:20:35,875 --> 00:20:37,166
Point-one kilograms.

609
00:20:37,250 --> 00:20:39,208
Bath towels
are really light, huh?

610
00:20:39,291 --> 00:20:40,666
Only one thing left to do.

611
00:20:40,750 --> 00:20:43,041
It seems the time has come
to remove the seal

612
00:20:43,125 --> 00:20:44,541
on this 4.9 kilogram
hairband.

613
00:20:44,625 --> 00:20:46,875
My Master explicitly
forbid me from doing so,

614
00:20:46,958 --> 00:20:50,666
but to maintain balance here on
this planet, I have no choice.

615
00:20:50,750 --> 00:20:53,166
Well, I don't actually
have to get on the scale

616
00:20:53,250 --> 00:20:55,000
since I all ready know
the result.

617
00:20:55,083 --> 00:20:56,291
Time for ice cream!

618
00:20:57,583 --> 00:20:59,291
[NENDOU]
Hey, guys!

619
00:20:59,375 --> 00:21:00,916
Let's have
a snowball fight!

620
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:03,625
Ahh! A snowball fight, eh?
Interesting!

621
00:21:03,708 --> 00:21:05,250
No matter what type
of fight,

622
00:21:05,333 --> 00:21:07,166
I will defeat Nendou!
I will!

623
00:21:07,250 --> 00:21:08,875
[BOYS]
Hairo, it's melting!

624
00:21:08,958 --> 00:21:10,666
I'll try again!
Aaarggh!

625
00:21:10,750 --> 00:21:12,333
[BOYS]
Hairo, it's melting!

626
00:21:12,416 --> 00:21:13,750
Huh?
What's happening?

627
00:21:13,833 --> 00:21:15,916
Hey, guys, look!
We made an igloo!

628
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:17,291
Come on, get in!

629
00:21:17,375 --> 00:21:19,041
[ALL]
Hairo, it's melting!

630
00:21:19,125 --> 00:21:20,125
It's melting!

631
00:21:20,208 --> 00:21:22,208
Why is this...
happening to me?

632
00:21:22,291 --> 00:21:23,875
[ALL]
Hairo, it's melting!

633
00:21:23,958 --> 00:21:24,916
It's melting!

634
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:26,958
[SAIKI]
Welcome to psychic's world.

635
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:31,208
[TERUHASHI] Seriously?
Nothing for me again?

636
00:21:31,291 --> 00:21:32,833
What's going on?

637
00:21:32,916 --> 00:21:36,166
How has Saiki not sent a reply
to my New Year's card yet?

638
00:21:36,250 --> 00:21:37,458
After going back and forth,

639
00:21:37,541 --> 00:21:38,750
I signed it with a heart!

640
00:21:38,833 --> 00:21:39,875
And still nothing?

641
00:21:39,958 --> 00:21:41,041
This isn't possible!

642
00:21:41,125 --> 00:21:42,458
There's gotta be
a reason!

643
00:21:42,541 --> 00:21:43,750
Ahh!
Could it be

644
00:21:43,833 --> 00:21:45,708
that he's afraid
I'll start hating him

645
00:21:45,791 --> 00:21:47,333
if he writes
the wrong thing?

646
00:21:47,416 --> 00:21:49,541
Maybe! Or maybe
his handwriting's so bad

647
00:21:49,625 --> 00:21:52,250
that he has to take
penmanship lessons first?

648
00:21:52,333 --> 00:21:53,583
That's possible,
right?

649
00:21:53,666 --> 00:21:55,708
Or maybe he wants
to keep me in suspense?

650
00:21:55,791 --> 00:21:57,875
Does he enjoy
torturing me like this?

651
00:21:57,958 --> 00:21:59,041
Making me worry?

652
00:21:59,125 --> 00:22:01,333
Who the hell does he think
he is, anyway?

653
00:22:01,416 --> 00:22:03,375
But, yeah,
That's possible, right?

654
00:22:03,458 --> 00:22:04,666
[SAIKI]
Now I'm torn.

655
00:22:04,750 --> 00:22:06,708
To get her interest in me
to go down,

656
00:22:06,791 --> 00:22:08,416
should I give her this,
or not?

657
00:22:08,500 --> 00:22:10,291
What do I do?

658
00:22:11,875 --> 00:22:13,791
♪

659
00:22:20,500 --> 00:22:22,708
[woman singing in Japanese]

660
00:23:41,666 --> 00:23:43,541
[SAIKI]
It's time for the preview

661
00:23:43,625 --> 00:23:45,666
of our next episode.
It's quiet this time.

662
00:23:45,750 --> 00:23:48,666
Maybe that's because I'm wearing
the telepathy silencer.

663
00:23:48,750 --> 00:23:50,791
For once, I can do
the preview the way I want.

664
00:23:50,875 --> 00:23:53,041
Next time on <i>The Disastrous</i>
<i>Life of Saiki K.</i>

665
00:23:53,125 --> 00:23:56,083
Kaidou has lots of lines to say.
Good luck with that.

